<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-16 09:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Mostly Up in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are mixed in today's early trading.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average is down 18 points in the early
going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-2
lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 20 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down a fraction.
</P>
<P>
   There was heavy volume during the opening minutes on the NYSE,
which likely was due to the session's triple-witching expirations
of stock index options, stock index futures and options on
individual stocks.
</P>
<P>
   In corporate news, a new warning about quarterly earnings came
from Xerox, which said its second-quarter results will fall below
expectations.
</P>
<P>
   High-tech firms Red Hat and Adobe Systems both posted
better-than-expected earnings after yesterday's closing bell.
</P>
<P>
   Meantime, a report on May housing construction shows further
signs of economic slowing.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are higher on that news, on the belief that the
Federal Reserve may need to do less tinkering with interest rates.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
