<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Dept. Loses Phone Service  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Heavy rains and the effects of a fire knocked
out all telephone service for about two hours at the State
Department.
</P>
<P>
   Even the sensitive operations center lost use of its telephones
during the outage Thursday night. Backup batteries that could have
been used to turn on some telephones were still out of commission
due to an unrelated fire in the department basement on Wednesday,
spokesman Philip Reeker said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   However, the U.S. official said there was no serious impact on
the department's operations.
</P>
<P>
   The telephones went out at about 8:40 p.m. EDT amid a heavy
downpour that knocked out service and trees in various parts of the
capital area. Repair crews with generators were summoned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
