<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-16 17:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bitter custody battle preceded murder of quads' mom, lawyer testifies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SAN ANTONIO (AP) - A South Texas millionaire voluntarily
terminated his parental rights after his ex-wife said for a second
time he had abused one of their two daughters, according to
testimony Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mr. Blackthorne terminated parental rights. He would have no
further rights and no further obligations, including the obligation
to pay child support,'' said Ken Nunley, one of the attorneys for
Sheila Bellush.
</P>
<P>
   Allen Blackthorne has been linked in the shooting and stabbing
death of Bellush - the mother of six including quadruplets - in her
Sarasota, Fla., home. He is charged with interstate conspiracy to
commit murder for hire and interstate domestic violence.
Blackthorne faces a mandatory life sentence on the charges.
</P>
<P>
   By relinquishing parental rights, Blackthorne would have no
legal ties to his two daughters. ''After this was signed, there was
no turning back,'' Nunley testified.
</P>
<P>
   Nunley also testified that in September 1997 neighbors of
Bellush sought custody of one of her daughters after Bellush was
accused hitting the girl with a belt.
</P>
<P>
   Nunley said the neighbors were represented by Blackthorne's
lawyers, who had months before been locked in a heated custody
battle with Bellush.
</P>
<P>
   The neighbors later dismissed their custody suit and child abuse
charges against Bellush were dropped. Bellush and her two daughters
with Blackthorne soon moved from San Antonio to Sarasota.
</P>
<P>
   Bellush was killed six weeks after moving from Texas. Her
2-year-old quadruplets from her second husband, Jamie Bellush, were
discovered unharmed, two of them crawling in their mother's blood.
Jamie Bellush and the children now live in Sussex County, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Blackthorne had terminated his parental rights in July 1997,
Nunley said, after Bellush alleged for a second time that he had
sexually abused one of the girls.
</P>
<P>
   The family court judge at that hearing testified Friday about
the bitter nature of the couple's dispute.
</P>
<P>
   ''From the beginning it was acrimonious, very acrimonious. There
were a lot of past hurts,'' said State District Judge Frank
Montalvo. ''It was obvious that all these folks wanted was to
settle the score.''
</P>
<P>
   The judge said he was ''shocked'' when Blackthorne asked to
relinquish his parental rights. He said Blackthorne was sobbing,
but did not seem sincere in his grief.
</P>
<P>
   The first abuse accusation against Blackthorne came during a
hearing in June 1993, when Blackthorne sued for increased
visitation rights.
</P>
<P>
   Mary Fenlon, Bellush's attorney at the time, testified Thursday
that Bellush intended to introduce allegations that Blackthorne
molested one of their two daughters.
</P>
<P>
   ''We broke for lunch and when we came back, Blackthorne and his
attorney were gone. They had dropped the suit,'' Fenlon testified
under questioning by prosecutor Richard Durbin.
</P>
<P>
   Under cross examination, previous court testimony was admitted
into evidence in which Stevie Bellush said her mother lied about
the allegations.
</P>
<P>
   Also Thursday, the jury heard details from a deposition Bellush
filed in her divorce from Blackthorne, in which she said
Blackthorne twice threatened to kill her and once to disfigure her
face.
</P>
<P>
   In other testimony this week, Blackthorne's golfing buddy said
he asked friends to lie on his behalf if police arrested him for
the slaying of the man's ex-wife.
</P>
<P>
   Daniel Rocha, 30, is serving a life prison term in Florida for
solicitation of capital murder in Bellush's slaying.
</P>
<P>
   His testimony has linked Blackthorne to Jose Luis Del Toro, the
alleged gunman. Rocha testified he proposed the killing to friend
Sammy Gonzales, who in turn hired his cousin Del Toro in the murder
scheme.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzales, who is serving a 19-year prison sentence in Florida,
also is expected to testify. He pleaded guilty to solicitation of
capital murder and testified against Rocha.
</P>
<P>
   During that trial, Gonzales said Rocha told him the money and
the murder plot came from Blackthorne.
</P>
<P>
   Del Toro, 23, a former high school football star in Uvalde, is
scheduled for trial next month in Florida.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
