	   GOSHEN, N.Y. (AP) - An Orange County Court judge has signed
orders of protection that could bar a student accused of rape from
attending high school in the fall.
</P>
<P>
   James Cox pleaded not guilty Thursday to charges he raped two
girls, ages 14 and 15.
</P>
<P>
   The 15-year-old girl attends Marlboro High School with Cox. She
already has an order of protection in the town of Newburgh but that
does not bar Cox from attending school with the girl.
</P>
<P>
   The order signed Thursday includes school grounds but the judge
said Cox, 17, can attend school next week for the one final exam he
has left. He also said Cox's lawyer could challenge the school
provision of the protection order.
</P>
