   Alan Joseph, Cox's lawyer, said the charges are as yet unproved
and argued the student has the right to a public education.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant District Attorney Kelle Grimmer said Cox has tried to
intimidate the girl at school and on one occasion the girl fainted
due to his presence in school.
</P>
<P>
