<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Xerox Corp., down $4.75 at $20.563
</P>
<P>
   The Stamford, Conn.-based business machines maker warned its
second-quarter earnings would likely be well below Wall Street's
expectations. The company attributed the shortfall to a mismanaged
reorganization of its sales force and problems in the Mexican
market.
</P>
<P>
UnionBanCal Corp., down $8.75 at $19.938
</P>
<P>
   The bank holding company lowered its second-quarter earnings
projection, saying it expects to post operating earnings of 77
cents to 82 cents a share. Analysts had expected earnings of 88
cents a share.
</P>
<P>
Nvest LP, up $17.625 at $37.625
</P>
<P>
   CDC Asset Management, the investment management arm of France's
Caisse des Depots Group, will buy the Boston-based investment
management company for $2.2 billion, which includes the assumption
of $1.5 billion of debt. Nvest is made up of 11 investment firms
and six investment sales and consulting firms.
</P>
<P>
Perot Systems Corp., down $2.875 at $11.125
</P>
<P>
   The Dallas-based provider of information technology services
warned that its second-quarter results would fall short of
expectations largely because of the loss of one client and reduced
business with a second.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Rambus Corp., up $19.313 at $76
</P>
<P>
   Toshiba Corp. signed a new licensing agreement to use Rambus'
computer-chip technology. Tokyo-based Toshiba is a computer and
electronics company.
</P>
<P>
Smith-Gardner &AMP; Associates, Inc., down $2.344 at $4.906
</P>
<P>
   The Delry Beach, Fla.-based maker of e-commerce software, warned
that it will report a second-quarter loss. Analysts had been
expecting the company to earn 10 cents a share.
</P>
<P>
RemedyTemp Inc., down $2.313 at $13.063
</P>
<P>
   The provider of customer-service technology services expects to
report fiscal third-quarter earnings that fall below Wall Street
analysts' expectations. The Aliso Viejo, Calif.-based company said
the shortfall was due to slower-than-expected sales in April and
May.
</P>
<P>
Covad Communications Group Inc., down $6.813 at $18.438
</P>
<P>
   The Internet service provider will acquire privately held
Bluestar Communications Inc. for $202 million in stock to get more
customers in the Southeast. Both companies provide high-speed
Internet access over the copper wires used by phone companies,
known as digital subscriber lines.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
