<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Couple Killed In Mexico  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUADALAJARA, Mexico (AP) -- An American couple was found Friday
shot to death in their home in western Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies of Norris and Nancy Price, 67 and 62 respectively,
were found Friday in their home in Ajijic, a lakeside community
near Guadalajara where many U.S. expatriates live, the U.S. Embassy
confirmed. Norris Price was president of the local golf club.
</P>
<P>
   Each had been shot once in the head through a pillow, and two
45-caliber bullet casings were found nearby, said spokesman Lino
Gonzalez of the Jalisco state attorney general's office.
</P>
<P>
   He said the suspected motive was a land dispute, though he
didn't offer details. He said the couple had been receiving
menacing phone calls since April. Nothing was missing from the
home.
</P>
<P>
   Four Americans have been slain in Ajijic in the last 2&AMP;frac12; years,
Gonzalez said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
