<HEADLINE> New York residents die in Florence County wreck  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FLORENCE, S.C. (AP) - Two New York residents died when their
vehicle ran off Interstate 95 and overturned several times, the
Highway Patrol says.
</P>
<P>
   Din Stephenson, 21, and Benetta Johnson, 25, both of Mount
Vernon, N.Y., died following the wreck Thursday morning. Each was
thrown from the vehicle, Coroner M.G. Matthews said.
</P>
<P>
   Stephenson, who was driving, ran off the road and lost control,
and the car, which had been traveling at about 80 mph, overturned
five times, Highway Patrol 1st Sgt. Jo Nell said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It looks like he might have fallen asleep at the wheel and
then lost control, but we can't say that for sure. I know they had
been traveling all night,'' Nell said.
</P>
<P>
   They were heading to Georgia when the wreck occurred at about
9:30 a.m. about six miles north of Florence.
</P>
<P>
   Stephenson died at the scene and Johnson died at a local
hospital, Matthews said.
</P>
</TEXT>
