<HEADLINE> 73-year-old motorcyclist pulled from river  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) - A 73-year-old motorcyclist remained in
critical condition Friday night after he flipped over a bridge and
fell 60 feet to the Susquehanna River.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred about 3:45 p.m. in the eastbound lane of
The River Bridge carrying Route 17 between Vestal and Endwell.
</P>
<P>
   Kimball Carroll of Endicott was riding his 1983 Suzuki
motorcycle to a routine inspection when he hit the curb and flipped
over the side, leaving the motorcycle on the bridge, investigators
told the Binghamton Press &AMP; Sun-Bulletin.
</P>
<P>
   Within 5 minutes, police and fire departments from surrounding
towns were tracking Carroll - still wearing his white motorcycle
helmet - downstream. He was pulled out about 4 p.m. at a park about
a mile downstream, brought ashore by a hovercraft.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue personnel performed cardiopulmonary resuscitation. State
police told the newspaper rescuers could not find vital signs until
about 4:15 p.m.
</P>
