<HEADLINE> Pacers Lead Lakers by 19 After 3  </HEADLINE>
By STEVE HERMAN
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Jalen Rose had 28 points and the Indiana
Pacers took an 86-67 lead over the Los Angeles Lakers going into
the fourth quarter of Game 5 in the NBA Finals Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Pacers, determined to stay alive in the best-of-seven
series, led 64-45 at halftime, took their biggest lead at 21 points
early in the third quarter and held off a brief Lakers rally that
cut the lead to 13 midway through the period.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana led by 15 points when Rik Smits picked up his fifth foul
and left with 4:47 remaining in the third quarter. But a basket and
two free throws by Rose pushed the lead back to 19. Then, after two
baskets by Shaquille O'Neal, Austin Croshere hit two free throws on
a flagrant foul by Rick Fox.
</P>
<P>
   The Pacers kept the ball, and eight seconds later Kobe Bryant
picked up his fifth foul and Mark Jackson hit two free throws to
give Indiana an 84-65 lead.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal, who had 29 points through three quarters, scored for the
Lakers before another basket by Jackson pushed Indiana's lead back
to 19 at the end of the period.
</P>
<P>
   No one besides O'Neal had more than 8 points for Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Eight 3-pointers, including four by Rose and three by Reggie
Miller, who had 18 points, helped Indiana take leads of up to 20
points in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Three straight baskets by Rose, including his fourth 3-pointer,
gave Indiana a 46-32 lead midway through the period.
</P>
<P>
   Travis Best, who bruised his shoulder in Game 4 and was
questionable until game time, scored two straight baskets in the
second quarter to push the Pacers' lead to 50-35. Rose then scored
two straight for a 54-35 lead.
</P>
<P>
   In the closing minutes of the half, Miller scored a basket and
then hit two free throws after Bryant picked up his third foul. The
biggest lead for Indiana in the first half was at 64-44 before
O'Neal hit one of two free throws with 10 seconds left in the half.
</P>
<P>
   The Pacers shot 75 percent and hit all six of their 3-point
attempts in the first quarter, which ended with them ahead 39-28.
The Lakers' only lead was after Glen Rice hit one of two free
throws at the start of the game to make it 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   A basket by Miller, a rebound basket by Smits and the first
3-pointer by Miller gave the Pacers a 7-1 lead before the first Los
Angeles basket, a 3-pointer by Ron Harper.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles tied the game at 9. But two free throws by Smits and
the first 3-pointer by Rose started another big Indiana run.
</P>
<P>
   Three minutes later, Miller hit his second 3-pointer and was
fouled by Harper on the play. He hit the free throw to complete the
four-point play for a 22-13 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The second 3-pointer by Rose made it 32-21, and his third
3-pointer in the closing seconds gave Indiana a 37-26 lead before
offsetting baskets by Robert Horry and Jackson at the end.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
