<HEADLINE> Trenton Thunder 1, Norwich Navigators 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Chris Reitsma fired six shutout innings in
his Double-A debut, and Bryce Florie and Jeff Taglienti combined
for three innings of shutout relief, as the Trenton Thunder (26-36)
defeated the Norwich Navigators, 1-0, in Eastern League play.
</P>
<P>
   Reitsma (1-0) retired the final 18 batters he faced
consecutively, allowed one run, no walks, and four strikeouts, and
got the win. Randy Flores (4-8) went eight innings, allowing seven
hits, one run, four walks, and six strikeouts, and suffered the
loss. Jeff Taglienti earned the save.
</P>
<P>
   The lone run of the game was scored in the third inning as Angel
Santos doubled to left center. Aaron Capista followed up with a
double of his own, scoring Santos from second.
</P>
<P>
   The Navigators fell to 32-33 with the loss.
</P>
</TEXT>
